6:
This place is absurdly large... Simply
going from one end of the path to
the other is exhausting.
13:
Probably not without Simon. He's the
one who opened it up for us last
time—
19:
You're not seriously trying to go
outside, are you?
22:
Plus... does he really live in that small
cabin over there?
25:
That can't be right... That's Grey's
home. I've never been inside, but I
know that's where he lived.
29:
Then we must take a closer look. Alk,
I think it's about time we resort to
force—
34:
No one told me we'd be going past
the town boundary! I've never put a
single toe outside before!
38: Why are you so against leaving?
42:
Because... the outside world is a
dangerous place with dragons
wandering around and stuff... isn't it?
45:
It's true there are dragons in the
world. But they aren't a problem.
52:
Come, Prika. We'll be fine as long as
we stick together.
57:
Fine, but you better stay glued to
me! Promise?
61:
Understood. I shall remain by your
side while we are beyond the
boundary.
65:
You lot... What are you doing with
the princess?
76:
Indeed. Nice to meet you, Princess
Prika. I am glad to see you well.
80:
Did my ears deceive me, or did you
just claim to MEET the princess?
You've been deceiving us?!
84:
Haha... This is ridiculous. Has the
princess charmed you to her side?
90:
Hold it right there, mister! Those
robes you're wearing look exactly
like Grey's!
92:
You know him, don't you? Where is
that old man?
98:
You still believe everything Grey has
told you about himself and about
you, don't you.
100:
But the truth is, you aren't a princess
who's meant for anything grand like
welcoming Mosnian royalty.
102:
In fact, you're no princess at
all—only a weapon leftover from the
fallen kingdom of Mosnia.
111:
Yours is a power that destroyed my
homeland long ago. It was meant to
be sealed away...
115:
What do you mean I'm a weapon?!
Nothing you're saying makes sense!
119:
Grey was supposed to be your
warden—nothing more, nothing less.
122: So then... I was his prisoner?
126:
Think about it. He never let you out
past the walls.
128:
Need I say more than that? Mosnia
is gone, and you are the remnant of
a bloodline fated to die.
136:
I thought outsiders like you would be
able to see the truth and dispose of
her for me... But I've made a grave
miscalculation.
139: There is only one path left.
144:
The poppets! They were YOUR
doing?!
147:
Weapons need to be controlled. I
happen to have inherited the
method.
150:
A decade's worth of magic sits in
this location... An endless supply of
mana, ripe for the taking!
156:
Everyone, get behind me! I get the
distinct feeling he won't be pulling
any punches!
161:
He's leaving us no choice. Get into
formation!
170:
Princess, it's time to open your
eyes—your power is a curse.
172: I shall prove it to you!
